 if something doesn't look quite right.<br><br>In digital sketching the problem is that you can't see the whole picture on-screen at full detail, so you'll have to constantly zoom out to make sure the head you were detailing isn't too big compared to the shoulders, etc. It's a real problem when you work with pictures sized at several-thousand-pixels-times-several-thousand-pixels.<br><br>This is one of the reasons why I use Flash for sketching. Since everything I draw is in vector format, I can easily select the head, re-size it to a correct size, and suffer absolutely no loss in image quality. You can't do that with pen and paper <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p><hr><b>Want to color my lineart?</b> Otherwise alter something I've created? Read my <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/ujspuonti.showPublicProfile?language=EN"><b>profile</b></a> for further information before proceeding!</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=4070.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showNextMessage?topicID=4070.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4070.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.emailToFriend?topicID=4070.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.threadControl?topicID=4070.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/delete